In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on March 29, 2018, he acknowledges National Cancer Control Month and expresses support for individuals fighting cancer. He thanks healthcare professionals, scientists, and researchers for their efforts in discovering a cure and mentions the decline in cancer-related deaths over the past two decades. The proclamation highlights American innovation and breakthroughs in cancer prevention and treatment, such as precision medicine and immunotherapy. Despite these advancements, the proclamation acknowledges the high number of lives lost to cancer, making it the second leading cause of death in the United States. It emphasizes the importance of prevention through healthy lifestyles, regular screenings, and awareness of family medical history. President Trump calls upon the American people to learn about preventative measures and participate in activities that increase awareness of cancer prevention and control. The proclamation concludes by inviting governors and officials to recognize National Cancer Control Month.